/-!
# Möbius Synthesis

This file assembles the final deviation bound (Proposition 3.6)
using the spatial synthesis / inclusion-exclusion strategy.
The proof combines:
- CRT multiplicativity of the counting function
  (`counting_function_multiplicative`)
- Product-difference expansion (`prod_sub_prod_expansion`)
- Triangle inequality (`Finset.abs_sum_le_sum_abs`)
- Small-divisor bounds via residue multiplicity estimates
  (`deviation_small_divisors` in `SmallDivisorHelpers.lean`)
- Large-divisor bounds via pointwise deviation estimates
  (`deviation_large_divisors`)
- Euler weight bounds (`EulerWeights.lean`)

## Main results

* `deviation_product_difference` — algebraic identity
  expressing the per-element deviation as a sum over
  nonempty subsets of prime factors of `q`.
* `deviation_triangle_bound` — triangle inequality bound
  on the absolute deviation.
* `deviation_final_synthesis` — the `q`-independent uniform
  bound `|D(q)| ≤ K · s(q)^{−δ}`.
* `deviation_uniform_exponent` — variant where the decay
  exponent `δ` is chosen independently of the box.
-/

